article.headline: Georgia Southern 111, Webber College  73
article.story: STATESBORO, Ga. (AP) -- Elton Nesbitt led five Georgia Southern players in double figures Tuesday night as the Eagles topped 100 points for this first time this season with a 111-73 victory over Webber International. It was the fifth straight win for Georgia Southern (9-4), and its 16th in a row at home. The Eagles, who finished with 57.4 percent shooting, jumped to a 9-0 lead before the Warriors (2-15) scored their first basket. A 3-pointer by Nesbitt gave GSU its largest lead of the half, 42-25, with under five minutes to play. The lead was 48-34 at intermission. An 8-2 run cut the lead to 65-48 with 13:44 remaining, but five minutes later GSU had extended its margin to 32. The Warriors' Juan Alvarez lead all scorers with 26 points. Louis Graham added 17 and Donte Gennie 16 for Georgia Southern, which also got 13 points from Jarek Swain and 10 from Dwayne Foreman.
